d in a wider inquiry conducted by Mr Iemma's office. General Sutiyoso's chief of staff, Suhendro Baskito, yesterday said his boss was undressed when the police entered his room. "He was asleep, the two police woke him up. They were standing at the side of his bed. "He asked 'Who are you?' and they explained that they were police officers and wanted him to appear at the inquiry into the East Timor killings. "He immediately called me. I was staying in the adjoining room. By the time I got there he was wearing shorts and a T-shirt." A spokeswoman for the Shangri-La Hotel yesterday repeated claims that police had demanded access to the room, which was provided by the duty manager, using a master key. Additional reporting: Paul Maley Iemma apology to Jakarta Jumping the gun in mill decision Coal trains at ports not fully loaded Outlook for blacks still far behind New magistrate was at fault as a lawyer Arroyo backs deal to tackle terror scourge Tamil Tigers set for blacklist We need help on al-Qa'ida: ASIO Extra pay for Afghan campaign Honour for air crash victims Law change to draw line through Tintin action Where there's water, there's growth. Get your FREE water investment kit today 1st mth best package + install 4 NOTHING*. HSBC's Low Rate Credit Card - Switch to HSBC's Low Rate Credit Card today and save. Apply now. Celebrate 60 yrs of Saab Free sat nav, 3 yrs servicing & auto trans. $4,300 value. Ends June 27 It won't just be another day at the office. See the full demo. Buy, sell or hold? Get 60 free recommendations in a 6-week trial of sharemarket advice. Try Weight Watchers Online and save
