urg following an overnight flight from Sierra Leone after attacking the "cynicism" of critics who described his diplomatic mission to the continent as a "vanity expedition". He delivered a passionate defence of his interventionist foreign policy in a speech at the University of South Africa Business School in Midrand, near the capital Pretoria. And he called for greater urgency from the international community to stop the bloodshed in the Sudanese province of Darfur and restore normality to Zimbabwe. Mr Blair also insisted that intervening to assist the poor nations of Africa was not only morally the right thing to do but also in the self-interest of the rich world. May 30: Blair defends Africa trip May 29: Blair heads to Africa on farewell tour Suicide verdict in teen&#39;s custody case A jury has returned a verdict of suicide on a 14-year-old who was the youngest person in Britain to die in custody. Piper and Evans in &#39;quickie&#39; divorce DJ Chris Evans and former Doctor Who actress Billie Piper have been granted a "quickie" divorce, it has been reported. ITV News wants to recruit &#39;Citizen Correspondents&#39; If you&#39;d like to get involved, and see your opinions feature in our programmes then click here to send us your details. We will contact you directly with more information on how to get your views on air. Free Yourself of Debt Clear up to 75% off what you owe. Government Insolvency Act can clear personal debt over Â£20k at Â£200 p/m. Get out of Debt Now Free report explains little known secrets and advice to clearing debt. Content &copy; ITV Network Limited. All rights reserved. Registered office: 200 Grays Inn Road, London WC1X 8XZ Registered in England number: 603893
