esentative Timothy Neale has commented, â€œWe have not gotten the lawsuit yet, so we are not commenting on it. We are not confirming the reports that Jeppesen did work for the CIA. The services Jeppesen provides are provided on a confidential basis for all its customers.â€ The suit alleges that the detainees were taken to countries where they underwent inhumane, degrading treatment and torture since they were beyond the reach of the law. The suit also states that Jeppesen provided services to the flight and crew used in the rendition program â€œto unlawfully render plaintiffs to detention and interrogation in Morocco, Egypt and Afghanistanâ€. The suspects were apprehended under the U.S. government's â€œextraordinary rendition programâ€. Extraordinary rendition is the clandestine capture and transfer of suspects to be detained and interrogated in countries where the protection of U.S. laws does not apply, said Ben Wizner, an ACLU attorney. He also said that â€œEither they knew or reasonably should have known that they were facilitating a torture program.â€ The content of this field is kept private and will not be shown publicly. Lines and paragraphs break automatically. to display uploaded files or images inline. You may quote other posts using You may quote other posts using to display uploaded files or images inline. More information about formatting options Username or e-mail address: Do you think Paris Hilton should be spared of punishment?: Health Updates from TheMedGuru Mental and Physical Torture Inflict Similar Trauma Strike grounds Scandinavian airline Dell faces suit over &#039;substandard&#039; Inspiron models De Niro fires back against lawsuit Lockheed & Boeingâ€™s ULA gets nod from FTC PPF (Public Provident Fund) What is the difference between demand draft and bankerâ€™s cheque? Learn how to start your own nursing agency f/s Samsung HL-P5063W 50 Wide-$600usd,Acer AT3201W 32 Widescreen LCD TV--------$400usd f/s PLAY STATION 3 AT JUST $200USD,XBOX 360 AT J