http://news.google.com/news/url?sa=T&ct=us/18-1&fd=R&url=http://www.wmur.com/news/13437256/detail.html&cid=1116940383&ei=iIBkRp-FDojsqgOG-ZSiBg Earthquakes Rattle N.H. Seacoast - Local News Story - WMUR Manchester As Seen On 9 As Seen On 9 Earthquakes Rattle N.H. Seacoast Officials Rule Out Methane Explosions As Cause Of Sounds POSTED: 10:39 am EDT June 4, 2007 Sign Up for Breaking News Alerts Three mild earthquakes were recorded in New Hampshire over the weekend. The Emergency Management Agency said the quakes hit Saturday night and Sunday afternoon in the Portsmouth-Exeter area. The earthquakes, which sounded like explosions, rattled a lot of wall photos and cupboard items but didn't cause any damage or injuries. Initially, officials investigated whether the explosive sounds were underground methane gas explosions. They found the gas escaping from the ground in Portsmouth on Saturday evening. But after comparing the times scores of 911 calls came in with the times recorded for the tremors, Assistant Fire Chief Steven Achilles said authorities have ruled out underground gas explosions as the cause of the ground-shaking. "Now that we can link the time of the 911 calls to specific events, we feel a lot more confident," said Achilles. He said all three incidents at 8 and 10:35 Saturday night and 2:35 Sunday afternoon coincided with seismic activity reported by emergency management officials. He said the methane gas discovery either was a coincidence or else caused by the earth tremors. The strongest of the quakes was centered seven miles southwest of Portsmouth. The second tremor Saturday night was centered 1.5 miles north of Exeter. . All rights reserved. This material may not be published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed. Company coming? Find out how to clean up fast! Interview Fashion Tips For Men Believe it or not, a man can lose out on a job opportunity because of his appearance, just as a woman can. Find out what not to wear. Refinance Your Home And Save E