ruggling to impose its authority on the anarchic nation. The posting could not be immediately verified but was on a site used by al Qaeda and other Islamists. (c) Reuters 2007. All rights reserved. Republication or redistribution of Reuters content, including by caching, framing or similar means, is expressly prohibited without the prior written consent of Reuters. Reuters and the Reuters sphere logo are registered trademarks and trademarks of the Reuters group of companies around the world. Iran says will not beg for its atomic rights Hospital spot checks to fight superbugs Inspired by Bollywood dad's film teen elopes Gates says no evidence Iran moving weapons to Taliban Iran calls U.S. missile interceptor plan a "joke" Man arrested for woman's murder Hilton begins jail term Bush heads to Europe for G8 "Pirates" soars to top of international box office Putin bashes West on G8 summit eve Putin bashes West on G8 summit eve Female hip-hop fights a bad rap Tiananmen quiet on anniversary of protest Pakistani elephant beats keeper when meals late Somali group says behind attack on premier Abe's support hits lowest since taking office Page 4 of 5 Is Cardinal O'Brien right in his warning to pro-abortion Catholic politicians? E-mail your questions to , leader of Edinburgh City Council, for publication in the June 10th Scotland on Sunday Decided on a last minute break? Click here to book a room with scotsman.com FREE property investment workshops in Scotland - Play SuperScotGames now and compete for fun, cash or prizes Meet friends old and new. Tickets from 10 pence Hotel & Theatre breaks from Â£63.50! Hotels worldwide from just Â£17, with The Scotsman View our selection of pictures from around Scotland on Election day D-Day landing on France, reported by The Scotsman 63 years ago this month. Journey into the past-FREE A full round up of Scottish business news at your desk by email every morning Scotland on Sunday Election Supplement 2007 Scotland on Sunday election blog Gay