 a helicopter charter owner, points out his helicopter never hover over buildings, according to the New York Daily News. "He's pretty much trying to beat up on the helicopter tourism industry," he said. "I am concerned about helicopters flying over a densely populated city," Weiner said. "I think it's dangerous, and I think it poses a threat." One has to wonder what New York Mayor Michael Bloomberg has to say about all this, considering he's a helicopter pilot and flies himself around the city. The mayor may be trying to find just the right words... as there have been no reports of a response as of yet. Mon, Jun 4 2007 Report: LEX Tower Backup Staffing Plan In Place, But Never Activated Mon, Jun 4 2007 Passengers Injured After Plane Impacts Homes Near CCB Mon, Jun 4 2007 More Chilling Details Revealed About Plot To Blow Up JFK Mon, Jun 4 2007 Carroll County Regional Airport Looking To Expand Sun, Jun 3 2007 Global Warming On Agenda At IATA Annual Meeting Agenda Sun, Jun 3 2007 FAA Reassures Pilots, AOPA That GPS Units Still OK For IFR Approaches Mon, Jun 4 2007 Southwest 737 Makes Emergency Landing At Oakland Airport Mon, Jun 4 2007 Brazil Supreme Court: US Pilots Cannot Be Compelled To Travel To Brazil Sun, Jun 3 2007 Boeing Subsidiary Sued On Behalf Of Al Qaida Suspects There are no events scheduled for the moment. Enter your email address and choose the Aero-Newsletters you want to be subscribed to. Do not subscribe me to this newsletter Subscribe me to the text version of this newsletter Subscribe me to the HTML version of this newsletter Subscribe me to the PDF version of this newsletter See all we have to offer Your browser is not properly configured to use Aero-News.net. Your problem may be one of the following: You are using a browser that is not supported by Aero-News.net. In order to fully appreciate all that we have to offer, we recommend that you upgrade to a browser supported by Aero-News.net: Microsoft Internet Explorer (Version 5 or later) Netscape (V