eader John A. Boehner issued a statement warning that he intended to bring up a privileged resolution demanding that the ethics committee investigate whether Jefferson should be expelled. This story originally appeared in CQ Today. &#160; &#160; &#160; | &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; | &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; Related Topics: Email this entry to: E-mail Address (for verification only; not for publication): &copy; 2007 &#8226; All Rights Reserved &#8226; Congressional Quarterly Inc. 1255 22nd Street N.W. &#8226; Washington, D.C. 20037 &#8226; 202-419-8500
